<font color="#FF0000">AMERICA'S ILLS &amp; VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Wed Feb  5 19:33:11 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
The entire Vietnam issue is simple.  Play chess every day for ten years for the chess world's praise and promise not to win; you  won't receive any praise; but you and the world knows you could win in 20 minutes.  Play NFL football for ten years against a high school team; but promise not to win a single game.  Play basketball for ten years for 10 million dollars per year; but promise not to win any games[but make 10 out of 10 3-pointers].  Go through High School with outstanding grades; but promise not to graduate. Now play war for ten years in Nam and promise not to win, when you know you could win in a week;  but in this case, do it for life and death for the nation's highest authority system on a poverty wage.  Then display the death and funerals of American Fighting Men for ten years on TV in the mornings, in the afternoons and in the evenings.  And today we wonder why the whole culture is rejecting all authority, avoiding stress with drugs, and distrusting everyone.  These issues in America seem clear to me.  Throw big money at drugs, education, immigration, AIDS, the deficit, young unwed mothers, garbage pale newborn, gangland murders and government taxation with IRS confiscation. Is there an answer?  Sure!  Apply cost effective measures of effectiveness to every social program. And, if he doesn't meet the target, fire him.  Like society did to Lyndon Johnson, MacNamara and others.  If I were an evil foreign power bent on destroying a nation from within, I would insure America continues on her current track.
